INSERT INTO `models` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `img_url`) VALUES
(2048, 'Air Max TW Trainer', 'Nike Air Max TW Trainers in Black and White. That quintessential laid-back look of ‘90s footwear collides with fast-paced 100 miles per hour modern culture in the form of the inimitable Air Max Tailwind. Taking its cues from the beloved franchise that introduced us to Nike Air Max cushioning and smoothed that tricky transition from sportswear to streetwear, this striking design ticks all the style and comfort boxes. The lightweight breathable engineered upper showcases angular and organic lines, whilst the 5 see-through windows underfoot deliver time-tested Air cushioning. Grippy rubber outsole for enhanced traction.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4081580.jpg'),
(2049, 'Air Force 1 Low Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 Low Trainer in White. Named after the iconic Air Force One, the USA President\'s personal Jet, this trainer lives up to its name. Being the first basketball shoe to be graced with Nikes Air Technology when it was released in 1982.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/008939.jpg'),
(2051, 'Air Max 95 Essential Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 95 Essential Trainers in Black, Dark Grey and Black. Lightweight cushioning with a streamlined aesthetic points towards an unparalleled comfortable ride. Visible Air-Sole unit hugs the full length PU midsole; waffle outsole for traction.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4033586.jpg'),
(2052, 'Air Force 1 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 Trainers in Anthracite, Wolf Grey, Cool Grey and Black. A classic basketball shoe that has been reinterpreted in countless ways over the years. This version is made with a smooth wolf grey leather upper and features anthracite accents on the Swoosh, heel tab, and outsole. Equipped with Nike Air technology in the heel for cushioning and comfort. A classic low-top cut and vulcanised durable rubber sole unit.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091585.jpg'),
(2054, 'Air VaporMax Plus Trainer', 'Nike Air VaporMax Plus Trainers in White. Fusing glories of the past with the next big thing, Nike takes the classic Air Max Plus model from 1998 and throws in the floating cage and padded upper, combining it with revolutionary VaporMax Air technology to really crank up those comfort levels. With a prominent arch inspired by a whale’s tail, iconic wavy fingers that resemble palm trees and ocean waves, bold gradient colours and full-length rubber outsole for durability and traction. Synthetic upper, handy pull tab and reflective design details. After the seven-year journey from conception to release, the Air VaporMax represents a new era in Nike innovation. To truly capture the feeling of \"running on air\", the designers restructured the Air unit to be attached directly to the upper. As you step down, each lug gets pushed into the Air unit, ramping up the pressure. Then, as you step off, the pressure releases creating springy bounce with superior flexibility.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/119156.jpg'),
(2055, 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07', 'The radiance lives on in the Nike Air Force 1 \'07, the basketball original that puts a fresh spin on what you know best: durably stitched overlays, clean finishes and the perfect amount of flash to make you shine.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/b7d9211c-26e7-431a-ac24-b0540fb3c00f/air-force-1-07-shoes-GjGXSP.png'),
(2056, 'Air Max 90 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Trainers in Wolf Grey. Originally designed for performance running, feel the purrrr of technical brilliance slot seamlessly into your everyday casual wear. Epitomising the 1990s world of art, music and culture, the striking aesthetics combine with a grippy Waffle outsole and visible lightweight Air cushioning to leave you walking on a cloud. Air technology first debuted in 1978, with its visible cousin later appearing in 1987 in the legendary Air Max 1’s.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4033318.jpg'),
(2057, 'Air Force 1 \'07 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 Trainers in White and Black. The seamless combination of on-court comfort and off-court panache is astounding as you introduce your feet to some legendary footwear here in the form of the irresistible Air Force 1 from Nike. Effortlessly fusing cushioned court comfort with off-duty panache, the AF-1’s luscious leather upper adds a crisp and slick aesthetic whilst the underfoot is taken care of by the Nike Air unit that delivers comfort you can rely on again and again. Low-cut padded ankle collar, foam midsole, perforated toe box and pivot circle grippy rubber outsole. Outlined Swoosh to sides and customary contrast AIR motif.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091557.jpg'),
(2059, 'Dunk Low DB Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low DB Trainers in White, Football Grey and Game Royal. Beautifully crafted from premium leather, this legendary basketball low-top showcases the well-loved panelled design, round toe and perforated toe box. Full lace closure, logo patch to tongue, branded heel counter and flat rubber sole. Originating in 1985 in a truly golden age of Jordan and basketball in general the transition to streetwear and skate boarding was inevitable, as was the symbol it has since become for self-expression.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095142.jpg'),
(2060, 'Air Max 95 Essential Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 95 Essential Trainers in Black, Track Red and Anthracite. Inspired by the human body, the inimitable Air Max 95 Essential sees the midsole representing the spine, graduated panels are the muscles, the lace loops are the shoe’s ribs and the mesh draping the upper is the skin. The breathable mesh upper features leather and synthetic leather reinforcements, whilst the innovative lacing system supplies a snug custom fit. Visible Air cushioning, and flex grooves in the grippy outsole bend with your foot for unrestrictive movement. Signature Nike branding throughout.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091457.jpg'),
(2061, 'Nike Dunk Low', 'The \'80s b-ball icon returns with classic details and throwback hoops flair. Channelling vintage style back onto the streets, its padded, low-cut collar lets you take your game anywhere—in comfort.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/dc282f24-e721-456f-b931-53b4f8ed1ae4/dunk-low-shoes-nF8W1z.png'),
(2062, 'Air Force 1 \'07 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 Trainers in Black and White. Introduce your feet to some legendary footwear here in the form of the irresistible Air Force 1 from Nike. Effortlessly fusing cushioned court comfort with off-duty panache, the AF-1’s luscious leather upper adds a crisp and slick aesthetic whilst the underfoot is taken care of by the Nike Air unit that delivers comfort you can rely on again and again. Low-cut padded ankle collar, foam midsole, perforated toe box and pivot circle grippy rubber outsole. Outlined Swoosh to sides and customary contrast AIR motif.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095114.jpg'),
(2063, 'Air VaporMax Plus Trainer', 'Nike Air VaporMax Plus Trainers in Black. 20 years since the Air Max Plus debut; Nike combine the striking silhouette with a translucent VaporMax sole unit, tuned Air branding and 3M reflective detail.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/119077.jpg'),
(2064, 'Air VaporMax Plus Trainer', 'Nike Air VaporMax Plus Trainers in Wolf Grey and Black. Fusing glories of the past with the next big thing, Nike takes the classic Air Max Plus model from 1998 and throws in the floating cage and padded upper, combining it with revolutionary VaporMax Air technology to really crank up those comfort levels. With a prominent arch inspired by a whale’s tail, iconic wavy fingers that resemble palm trees and ocean waves, bold gradient colours and full-length rubber outsole for durability and traction. Synthetic upper, handy pull tab and reflective design details. After the seven-year journey from conception to release, the Air VaporMax represents a new era in Nike innovation. To truly capture the feeling of \"running on air\", the designers restructured the Air unit to be attached directly to the upper. As you step down, each lug gets pushed into the Air unit, ramping up the pressure. Then, as you step off, the pressure releases creating springy bounce with superior flexibility.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/123219.jpg'),
(2065, 'React Vision Trainer', 'Nike React Vision Trainers in Black, Anthracite and Black. Comfort of this magnitude doesn’t come around often; the React Vision skilfully combines lushly layered textures, vivid colours and a revolutionary seamless mesh upper complete with subtle pattern. Nike’s React foam offers up supreme all-day comfort whilst the deluxe tongue teams up with the padded heel for comfort you can trust. Eye-catching DIY-like exposed stitching, patchwork eye stays, D/MS/X label on pull tabs and insole, outlined Swoosh logo and rubber pods on the sole that boost the robustness and grip.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4041895.jpg'),
(2066, 'Air Max TW Trainer', 'Nike Air Max TW Trainers in Black and Anthracite. That quintessential laid-back look of ‘90s footwear collides with fast-paced 100 miles per hour modern culture in the form of the inimitable Air Max Tailwind. Taking its cues from the beloved franchise that introduced us to Nike Air Max cushioning and smoothed that tricky transition from sportswear to streetwear, this striking design ticks all the style and comfort boxes. The lightweight breathable engineered upper showcases angular and organic lines, whilst the 5 see-through windows underfoot deliver time-tested Air cushioning. Grippy rubber outsole for enhanced traction.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4084282.jpg'),
(2067, 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 LV8', 'The radiance lives on in the Nike Air Force 1 \'07 LV8. Crossing hardwood comfort with off-court flair, these kicks put a fresh spin on a hoops classic. Soft suede overlays pair with era-echoing \'80s construction and reflective-design Swoosh logos to bring you nothing-but-net style while hidden full-length Air units add the legendary comfort you know and love.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/b3546974-0d23-4657-a8a7-8d6abc9fc5e8/air-force-1-07-lv8-shoes-ggb31G.png'),
(2068, 'Air Max 270 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 270 Trainers in Smoke Grey, Black and Bright Mandarin. Legendary Air gets itself some extra Airtime at Footasylum here as the formidable Air Max 270 combines bold style with plush cushioning and cutting-edge innovations. Lightweight airy upper, cushioned low cut collar, stretchy inner sleeve and a bootie construction that gets up closed and personal. Foam midsole that puts a real spring in your step, Max Air unit to heel for long-lasting comfort and an extra-large window that delivers a bold style, pull tab to heel and grippy rubber outsole to complete.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091572.jpg'),
(2069, 'Air Max 90 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Trainers in Anthracite, Reflect Silver and Industrial Blue. Originally designed for performance running, feel the purrrr of technical brilliance slot seamlessly into your everyday casual wear. Epitomising the 1990s world of art, music and culture, the striking aesthetics combine with a grippy Waffle outsole and visible lightweight Air cushioning to leave you walking on a cloud. Air technology first debuted in 1978, with its visible cousin later appearing in 1987 in the legendary Air Max 1’s.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095120.jpg'),
(2070, 'Air Max 95 Essential Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 95 Essential Trainers in Black, Pure Platinum and Anthracite. Inspired by the human body, the inimitable Air Max 95 Essential sees the midsole representing the spine, graduated panels are the muscles, the lace loops are the shoe’s ribs and the mesh draping the upper is the skin. The breathable mesh upper features leather and synthetic leather reinforcements, whilst the innovative lacing system supplies a snug custom fit. Visible Air cushioning, and flex grooves in the grippy outsole bend with your foot for unrestrictive movement. Signature Nike branding throughout.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095133.jpg'),
(2071, 'Air Force 1 \'07 3 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 3 Trainers in White and Black. This low-cut take on the iconic Air Force 1 silhouette skilfully fuses a classic court aesthetic with a bold fashion-friendly look. Nike Air cushioning, perforated toe box and non-marking outsole.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/133491.jpg'),
(2072, 'Air Max 90 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Trainers in White. Originally designed for performance running, feel the purrrr of technical brilliance slot seamlessly into your everyday casual wear. Epitomising the 1990s world of art, music and culture, the striking aesthetics combine with a grippy Waffle outsole and visible lightweight Air cushioning to leave you walking on a cloud. Air technology first debuted in 1978, with its visible cousin later appearing in 1987 in the legendary Air Max 1’s.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4033317.jpg'),
(2073, 'Air Jordan 4 Craft', 'Fall in love with Olive. This edition of the \'89 classic features suede, leather and textiles done up in elegant earth tones. The signature mesh-inspired side panels are embossed for a tactile take on the original. And all the other iconic AJ4 elements are there too—like the floating eyestays, wavy mudguard and Jumpman branding.\nSKU: FB9927-200', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_prod_ss/w_640,c_limit,f_auto/96ea936e-7795-4b9e-a012-8d4d25157588/air-jordan-4-craft-olive-fb9927-200-release-date.jpg'),
(2074, 'Air Huarache Runner Trainer', 'Nike Air Huarache Runner Trainers in Black, Medium Ash and Anthracite. A rework on the classic Huarache silhouette, the plush running-inspired cushioned outsole remains but now sat atop a more stable and constructed upper. Lashings of leather and suede panels throughout, understated swoosh branding and a rubber waffle outsole tread for added grip.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091569.jpg'),
(2075, 'Air Max Pulse Trainer', 'Nike Air Max Pulse Trainers in Black and Anthracite. With its finger firmly on the Pulse and drawing its inspiration from the London music scene, an underground vibe is cleverly introduced to the proceedings. This legendary Air Max line boasts a textile-wrapped midsole and vacuum-sealed accents to maintain a vibrant aesthetic. With point-loaded Air cushioning revamped from the Air Max 270 that offers up improved bounce, leather and synthetic overlays, foam midsole, rubber waffle outsole and a versatile sporty aesthetic that will improve any outfit.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091575.jpg'),
(2076, 'React Vision Trainer', 'Nike React Vision Trainers in Anthracite, Reflective Silver and Industrial Blue. Comfort of this magnitude doesn’t come around often; the React Vision skilfully combines lushly layered textures, vivid colours and a revolutionary seamless mesh upper complete with subtle pattern. Nike’s React foam offers up supreme all-day comfort whilst the deluxe tongue teams up with the padded heel for comfort you can trust. Eye-catching DIY-like exposed stitching, patchwork eye stays, D/MS/X label on pull tabs and insole, outlined Swoosh logo and rubber pods on the sole that boost the robustness and grip.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095146.jpg'),
(2077, 'Flight \'89 Trainer', 'Nike Flight \'89 Trainers in Light Smoke Grey, White and Black. Starting off life as a basketball performance silhouette back in 1989, fast forward to 2022 and that distinctive vintage aesthetic is still evident. With a lush leather upper, bold contrast trims, secure lace fastening, and large Air Flight branding to tongue. Visible Air sole unit, embroidered heel branding and famous Nike Swoosh to sides.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4097639.jpg'),
(2078, 'Air Jordan 4', 'New fire. Reigniting a beloved brand colour, the AJ4 \'Red Cement\' brings a heritage twist to the buzzer-beating silhouette. Fire Red accents with a speckle effect recall the original \'White Cement\' colourway, and crisp white leather keeps every outfit feeling clean.\nSKU: DH6927-161', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_prod_ss/w_640,c_limit,f_auto/21570299-6494-47c1-b583-93903ec82552/air-jordan-4-red-cement-dh6927-161-release-date.jpg'),
(2080, 'Air Max 95 Essential Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 95 Essential Trainers in White and Grey Fog. Inspired by the human body, the inimitable Air Max 95 Essential sees the midsole representing the spine, graduated panels are the muscles, the lace loops are the shoe’s ribs and the mesh draping the upper is the skin. The breathable mesh upper features leather and synthetic leather reinforcements, whilst the innovative lacing system supplies a snug custom fit. Visible Air cushioning, and flex grooves in the grippy outsole bend with your foot for unrestrictive movement. Signature Nike branding throughout.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4037511.jpg'),
(2081, 'Dunk Low Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low Trainers in Mica Green and White. Say hello to spring with the latest Nike Dunk to land at Footasylum. A Photon Dust canvas base and Mica Green canvas tongue elevate this spring silhouette with matching Mica Green laces and leather overlays. A tumbled off-white Swoosh finishes off the trainer and gives a vintage aesthetic perfect for pairing with your favourite cargo shorts. An icon since 1985, the Nike Dunk is a must-have in every rotation.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4088684.jpg'),
(2082, 'Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Trainer', 'Nike Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Trainers in Black and Black Anthracite. The Air VaporMax 2023 lights the way towards that ‘walking on Air’ sensation that only Nike can provide. Awash with innovative tech via the removable perforated sock liner and stretchy Flyknit upper that’s made from at least 20% recycled content by weight. The one-piece Air unit that patrols the entire length of the shoe allows for smoother transitions and throws in unreal levels of cushioning. Standard lacing, seamless collar that sculpts the ankle reducing hot spots, and grippy rubber outsole. After the 7-year journey from conception to release, the Air VaporMax represents a new era in Nike innovation. To truly capture the feeling of \"running on air\", the designers restructured the Air unit to be attached directly to the upper. As you step down, each lug gets pushed into the Air unit, ramping up the pressure. Then, as you step off, the pressure releases creating springy bounce with superior flexibility.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091565.jpg'),
(2084, 'Air Max 90 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Trainers in Light Smoke Grey and Summit White. Originally designed for performance running, feel the purrrr of technical brilliance slot seamlessly into your everyday casual wear. Epitomising the 1990s world of art, music and culture, the striking aesthetics combine with a grippy Waffle outsole and visible lightweight Air cushioning to leave you walking on a cloud. Air technology first debuted in 1978, with its visible cousin later appearing in 1987 in the legendary Air Max 1’s.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095117.jpg'),
(2085, 'Nike Go FlyEase', 'Ditch the laces and get outside. These kicks feature Nike\'s revolutionary FlyEase technology, making on-and-off a breeze. With a heel that pivots open for a totally hands-free entry, they\'re great for people with limited mobility—or anyone who wants a quicker way to get going.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/c76e2119-acb7-4944-9085-d4f5ae2bda4a/go-flyease-easy-on-off-shoes-WS84pD.png'),
(2086, 'Dunk Low Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low Trainers in Black, Grey and Green Strike. This magnificent vintage is remarkably almost 40 years old looks as fresh in 2023 as it did when it was originally unleashed back in the mid 1980s. Smooth leather and suede upper with secure lace fastening closure, foam midsole, contrasting overlays, breathable perforations to toe box and rubber outsole. Classic Swoosh branding. Born from a series of mash-ups, hacks and tight deadlines, the Nike Dunk landed on US university basketball courts during the \'85–\'86 season. While the original \'College Colours\' designs helped fans stay true to their school, the Dunk didn\'t prove to be popular. But it was this humble sneaker\'s lack of popularity—and flat, grippy soles—that helped it jump the rails to captivate skateboarders. Decades later, this everyday favourite continues to be snatched up in countless colourways, proving its influence is undeniable.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4102059.jpg'),
(2087, 'Pegasus Trail 4 GORE-TEX Trainer', 'Nike Pegasus Trail 4 GORE-TEX Trainers in Black, Wolf Grey and Reflect Silver. The perfect accompaniment for those nastier weather conditions with its waterproof GORE-TEX layer keeping your feet dry and comfortable leaving you free to push your boundaries. Featuring less rubber in the outsole to seamlessly create a smooth transition from road to trail. Equipped with a full-length React midsole that offers up a responsive ride via its durable foam construction. The outsole wraps round the front for added durability combined with a generative traction pattern for optimal traction whatever the surface. Updated materials around the ankle helps to ensure that water and debris don’t get into the shoe. Nike Swoosh branding.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4102986.jpg'),
(2088, 'Air Max 270 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 270 Trainers in White and Black. Legendary Air gets itself some extra Airtime at Footasylum here as the formidable Air Max 270 combines bold style with plush cushioning and cutting-edge innovations. Lightweight airy upper, cushioned low cut collar, stretchy inner sleeve and a bootie construction that gets up closed and personal. Foam midsole that puts a real spring in your step, Max Air unit to heel for long-lasting comfort and an extra-large window that delivers a bold style, pull tab to heel and grippy rubber outsole to complete.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/118749.jpg'),
(2089, 'Dunk Hi Trainer', 'Nike Dunk High Grey White Looking for a clean silhouette to add to your Dunk rotation? We\'ve got you. The Nike Dunk High Grey White features an easy-to-style monochrome colour palette that will go with everything in your collection. A stone grey leather base allows off-white overlays, mudguards, eye stays and Swoosh to take centre stage. An icon on and off the courts since 1985, the Nike Dunk has become the must-have trainer of 2023. Fusing footwear and culture the Nike Dunk is a cultural icon that represents way more than just a fresh pair of sneaks.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4084974.jpg'),
(2090, 'Nike Dunk Low Retro', 'Recognising the Dunk\'s roots as the top-ranking university-team sneaker, the Be True To Your School Pack looks to the original ad campaign for inspiration. Colours represent top-flight universities, while crisp leather has the perfect amount of sheen to make \'em a hands-down win. So lace up and show off that varsity spirit. Are you game?', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/9f5d3ab4-98b4-44fe-9823-3b409603b520/dunk-low-retro-shoes-p6gmkm.png'),
