(2118, 'Air Max Pulse Trainer', 'Nike Air Max Pulse Trainers in Black, White and Pure Platinum. With its finger firmly on the Pulse and drawing its inspiration from the London music scene, an underground vibe is cleverly introduced to the proceedings. This legendary Air Max line boasts a textile-wrapped midsole and vacuum-sealed accents to maintain a vibrant aesthetic. With point-loaded Air cushioning revamped from the Air Max 270 that offers up improved bounce, leather and synthetic overlays, foam midsole, rubber waffle outsole and a versatile sporty aesthetic that will improve any outfit.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095109.jpg'),
(2119, 'Air Force 1 \'07 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 Trainers in White and Honey Dew. The seamless combination of on-court comfort and off-court panache is astounding as you introduce your feet to some legendary footwear here in the form of the irresistible Air Force 1 from Nike. Effortlessly fusing cushioned court comfort with off-duty panache, the AF-1’s luscious leather upper adds a crisp and slick aesthetic whilst the underfoot is taken care of by the Nike Air unit that delivers comfort you can rely on again and again. Low-cut padded ankle collar, foam midsole, perforated toe box and pivot circle grippy rubber outsole. Outlined Swoosh to sides and customary contrast AIR motif.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095113.jpg'),
(2120, 'Air Max 90 GTX Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 GTX Trainers in Summit White and Lapis Hemp. A weatherized version of the classic Nike Air Max 90, a waterproof GORE-TEX upper to keep your feet dry in wet conditions, as well as a durable leather vamp for added protection. The shoe also retains the iconic Air Max bubble unit in the heel for responsive cushioning.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095123.jpg'),
(2121, 'Air Huarache Runner Trainer', 'Nike Air Huarache Runner Trainers in Cargo Khaki, White and Sequoia. A rework on the classic Huarache silhouette, the plush running-inspired cushioned outsole remains but now sat atop a more stable and constructed upper. Lashings of leather and suede panels throughout, understated swoosh branding and a rubber waffle outsole tread for added grip.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095130.jpg'),
(2122, 'Nike Dunk Low', 'Created for the hardwood but taken to the streets, the \'80s basketball icon returns with classic details and throwback hoops flair. Durable leather and Ripstop textiles are paired with reflective design details and a frosted blue outsole for a sturdy construction that helps you face harsh conditions. And its padded, low-cut collar lets you take your game anywhere—in comfort.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/938273c4-d731-4fe6-b2c7-1a75002a1536/dunk-low-shoes-7CMvkH.png'),
(2123, 'Air Max TW Trainer', 'Nike Air Max TW Trainers in Wolf Grey and Rugged Orange. That quintessential laid-back look of ‘90s footwear collides with fast-paced 100 miles per hour modern culture in the form of the inimitable Air Max Tailwind. Taking its cues from the beloved franchise that introduced us to Nike Air Max cushioning and smoothed that tricky transition from sportswear to streetwear, this striking design ticks all the style and comfort boxes. The lightweight breathable engineered upper showcases angular and organic lines, whilst the 5 see-through windows underfoot deliver time-tested Air cushioning. Grippy rubber outsole for enhanced traction.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095138.jpg'),
(2124, 'Dunk Low Retro Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low Retro Trainers in Photon Dust, White and Racer Blue. A Kentucky-inspired colorway that was initially released in April 2023.tumbled leather base with blue smooth leather overlays for added contrast, swoosh sits to side in white. while the tongue tags and heel tabs are blue. The perfect summer sneaker to show off any outfit.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4096302.jpg'),
(2125, 'Blazer Mid \'77 Vintage Trainer', 'Nike Blazer Mid 77 Vintage Trainers in White and Black. A classic all-round sneaker that is blessed with a luxurious premium leather upper and a rich vintage aesthetic. Soft suede detailing, cushioned collar and contrast side Swoosh.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4033336.jpg'),
(2126, 'Air Max 90 LTR Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 LTR Trainers in Black. Some 30 years after the original release of this benchmark shoe, the low-top legend gets itself a premium leather revamp. Visible Max Air unit and full length rubber sole with flexible grooves.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4041849.jpg'),
(2127, 'Nike Air Force 1 Luxe', 'Crafted with precision, the Nike Air Force 1 Luxe refreshes the b-ball icon. Its crisp leather in the upper features the perfect shine. Stitching along the midsole adds an artisan touch while the rugged tread on the outsole nods to your favourite city boots.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/954de8c3-8422-49c2-81cb-bcbb69018760/air-force-1-luxe-shoes-RdCB1l.png'),
(2128, 'Air Max 90 LTR Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 LTR Trainers in White. Some 30 years after the original release of this benchmark shoe, the low-top legend gets itself a premium leather revamp. Visible Max Air unit and full length rubber sole with flexible grooves.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4041850.jpg'),
(2129, 'Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Trainers in Rattan, Dark Smoke Grey and Khaki. Next up for Nike’s “Next Nature” series is this sustainable re-working of the iconic Air Max 90. Almost indistinguishable from its traditional counterpart, the lushly layered upper consists of a robust ripstop base and durable overlays, all sat upon visible Nike Air technology. The semi-translucent midsole and crater speckled outsole provide aesthetically pleasing backup. Signature Nike branding together with handy heel and tongue pull loops. This magnificent silhouette boasts around 20% recycled materials by weight, so your footprint on the earth is less impact but in no way less stylish.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4065840.jpg'),
(2130, 'Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Trainers in Summit White, Light Iron Ore and Photon Dust. Next up for Nike’s “Next Nature” series is this sustainable re-working of the iconic Air Max 90. Almost indistinguishable from its traditional counterpart, the lushly layered upper consists of a robust ripstop base and durable overlays, all sat upon visible Nike Air technology. The semi-translucent midsole and crater speckled outsole provide aesthetically pleasing backup. Signature Nike branding together with handy heel and tongue pull loops. This magnificent silhouette boasts around 20% recycled materials by weight, so your footprint on the earth is less impact but in no way less stylish.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4070826.jpg'),
(2131, 'Dunk Low Retro Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low Retro Trainers in Football Grey, Midnight Navy and White. A versatile and stylish sneaker that is perfect for everyday wear. The upper is made of a premium leather and synthetic blend that is both durable and comfortable. The muted grey colorway is understated yet eye-catching, and the subtle pops of navy and aqua add a touch of personality. The mini swoosh on the side adds a modern touch, and the rubber outsole provides traction and durability. Whether you\'re looking for a sneaker to wear to the gym, to class, or just to run errands, the Nike Dunk Low Mini Swoosh Grey Navy is a great option. It\'s comfortable, stylish, and versatile, and it\'s sure to turn heads wherever you go.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091556.jpg'),
(2132, 'Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Trainer', 'Nike Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Trainers in Sand Drift and Bronzine. The Air VaporMax 2023 lights the way towards that ‘walking on Air’ sensation that only Nike can provide. Awash with innovative tech via the removable perforated sock liner and stretchy Flyknit upper that’s made from at least 20% recycled content by weight. The one-piece Air unit that patrols the entire length of the shoe allows for smoother transitions and throws in unreal levels of cushioning. Standard lacing, seamless collar that sculpts the ankle reducing hot spots, and grippy rubber outsole. After the 7-year journey from conception to release, the Air VaporMax represents a new era in Nike innovation. To truly capture the feeling of \"running on air\", the designers restructured the Air unit to be attached directly to the upper. As you step down, each lug gets pushed into the Air unit, ramping up the pressure. Then, as you step off, the pressure releases creating springy bounce with superior flexibility.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091567.jpg'),
(2133, 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07', 'The radiance lives on in the Nike Air Force 1 \'07, the b-ball icon that puts a fresh spin on what you know best: crisp leather, bold colours and the perfect amount of flash to make you shine.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/350e7f3a-979a-402b-9396-a8a998dd76ab/air-force-1-07-shoe-Pbt0tj.png');
INSERT INTO `models` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `img_url`) VALUES
(2134, 'Air Max 90 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Trainers in Summit White and Red Stardust. Originally designed for performance running, feel the purrrr of technical brilliance slot seamlessly into your everyday casual wear. Epitomising the 1990’s world of art, music and culture, the striking aesthetics combine with a grippy Waffle outsole and visible lightweight Air cushioning to leave you walking on a cloud. Air technology first debuted in 1978, with its visible cousin later appearing in 1987 in the legendary Air Max 1’s.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091577.jpg'),
(2135, 'Air Huarache Runner Trainer', 'Nike Air Huarache Runner Trainers in Light Smoke Grey, Iron Grey and Pewter. This most distinctive of shoes was first unleashed in 1991 with legendary designer Tinker Hatfield combining the fit of neoprene water ski-boots with the functionality of South American sandals. The Huarache first found its way to basketball courts before filtering out to streets where it earned its now much-deserved status. The Air Huarache moulds a classic aesthetic with a running-inspired design and a deluxe mixture of materials. Made with stretchy snug fabric, with variable-width lacing, futuristic heel cage and an elongated tongue that maintains that early 1990s vibe.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091583.jpg'),
(2136, 'Air Force 1 \'07 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 Trainers in Wolf Grey, White and Hyper Turquoise. Introduce your feet to some legendary footwear here in the form of the irresistible Air Force 1 from Nike. Effortlessly fusing cushioned court comfort with off-duty panache, the AF-1’s luscious leather upper adds a crisp and slick aesthetic whilst the underfoot is taken care of by the Nike Air unit that delivers comfort you can rely on again and again. Low-cut padded ankle collar, foam midsole, perforated toe box and pivot circle grippy rubber outsole. Outlined Swoosh to sides and customary contrast AIR motif.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095115.jpg'),
(2137, 'Air Max TW Trainer', 'Nike Air Max TW Trainers in Anthracite, Industrial Blue and Cool Grey. That quintessential laid-back look of ‘90s footwear collides with fast-paced 100 miles per hour modern culture in the form of the inimitable Air Max Tailwind. Taking its cues from the beloved franchise that introduced us to Nike Air Max cushioning and smoothed that tricky transition from sportswear to streetwear, this striking design ticks all the style and comfort boxes. The lightweight breathable engineered upper showcases angular and organic lines, whilst the 5 see-through windows underfoot deliver time-tested Air cushioning. Grippy rubber outsole for enhanced traction.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095125.jpg'),
(2138, 'Air Max Pulse Trainer', 'Nike Air Max Pulse Trainers in Light Bone, Particle Grey and College Grey. With its finger firmly on the Pulse and drawing its inspiration from the London music scene, an underground vibe is cleverly introduced to the proceedings. This legendary Air Max line boasts a textile-wrapped midsole and vacuum-sealed accents to maintain a vibrant aesthetic. With point-loaded Air cushioning revamped from the Air Max 270 that offers up improved bounce, leather and synthetic overlays, foam midsole, rubber waffle outsole and a versatile sporty aesthetic that will improve any outfit.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095135.jpg'),
(2139, 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 LV8', 'The radiance lives on in the Nike Air Force 1 \'07 LV8. Crossing hardwood comfort with off-court flair, this hoops original puts a fresh spin on everything you know best about the AF-1. Era-echoing \'80s construction pairs with crisp white real and synthetic leather and a reflective design Swoosh logo to bring you nothing-but-net style.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/e8e242bb-e086-4113-8f31-621a199f04e8/air-force-1-07-lv8-shoes-hwMtDD.png'),
(2140, 'Dunk Low Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low Trainers in Black, White and Optic Yellow. This magnificent vintage is remarkably almost 40 years old looks as fresh in 2023 as it did when it was originally unleashed back in the mid 1980’s. Smooth leather upper with secure lace fastening closure, foam midsole, contrasting overlays, breathable perforations to toe box and rubber outsole. Classic Swoosh branding. Born from a series of mash-ups, hacks and tight deadlines, the Nike Dunk landed on US university basketball courts during the \'85–\'86 season. While the original \'College Colours\' designs helped fans stay true to their school, the Dunk didn\'t prove to be popular. But it was this humble sneaker\'s lack of popularity—and flat, grippy soles—that helped it jump the rails to captivate skateboarders. Decades later, this everyday favourite continues to be snatched up in countless colourways, proving its influence is undeniable.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4102060.jpg'),
(2141, 'Blazer Low \'77 Vintage Trainer', 'Nike Blazer Low \'77 Vintage Trainers in White, Sail and Black. With its dashing heritage basketball looks and comfort personified construction, low-profile perfection makes a welcome detour to Footasylum. Initially designed for shooting hoops, this faithful remake provides a look and feel that is great for everyday casual wear. A premium leather upper is complemented by deluxe suede detailing that offers up a vintage aesthetic on top of the high durability factor. Squeaky clean colours, minimal lines, and a comfortable padded collar. The solid rubber outsole comes equipped with a herringbone pattern that enhances traction and resilience. Timeless Swoosh branding.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4050462.jpg'),
(2142, 'Huarache Trainer', 'Nike Huarache Trainers in Black and Anthracite. First released in 1991, esteemed footwear designer Tinker Hatfield wished to combine the fit of neoprene water-ski boots with the sheer functionality of South American sandals. Thirty years later, this instant classic is still a favourite on the basketball courts and on the streets where it really earned respect. With a plush foam midsole that is soft and springy, the distinctive heel clip and minimal branding channel a real early 1990’s vibe. Soft leather and airy neoprene-like fabric combine for laid-back styling. Cushioned inner sleeve, durable grippy rubber outsole and variable-width lacing enhance your comfort whilst perforations allow for increased breathability. Huarache motif to tongue.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4063271.jpg'),
(2143, 'Flight \'89 Trainer', 'Nike Flight \'89 Trainers in Black and White. Starting off life as a basketball performance silhouette back in 1989, fast forward to 2022 and that distinctive vintage aesthetic is still evident. With a lush leather upper, bold contrast trims, secure lace fastening, and large Air Flight branding to tongue. Visible Air sole unit, embroidered heel branding and famous Nike Swoosh to sides.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4081591.jpg'),
(2144, 'Nike React Vision', 'The Nike React Vision is a story of surreal comfort. Layered textures, shapes and vivid colours are combined in a design influenced by the exaggerated world of our dreams, while React foam and an ultra-plush tongue provide surreal comfort.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/18f06b19-1f30-4579-8613-ab72339676a7/react-vision-shoe-7SRnjk.png'),
(2145, 'Air Max Pulse Trainer', 'Nike Air Max Pulse Trainers in Summit White, Black and Pure Platinum. With its finger firmly on the Pulse and drawing its inspiration from the London music scene, an underground vibe is cleverly introduced to the proceedings. This legendary Air Max line boasts a textile-wrapped midsole and vacuum-sealed accents to maintain a vibrant aesthetic. With point-loaded Air cushioning revamped from the Air Max 270 that offers up improved bounce, leather and synthetic overlays, foam midsole, rubber waffle outsole and a versatile sporty aesthetic that will improve any outfit.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091574.jpg'),
(2146, 'Air More Uptempo 96 Trainer', 'Nike Air More Uptempo \'96 Trainers in Light Iron Ore, Industrial Blue, Black and White. Rocking 1990’s graffiti-styled graphics and sat atop visible Air cushioning, the Air More Uptempo ’96 absolutely nails down a jaw dropping off-court aesthetic. Originally designed for performance hoops, the Max Air unit is both lightweight and durable. The elastic straps that run across the top of the foot allow you to wear them laced or unlaced, whilst the round laces match the round pull tabs for another great style point. Interior graphics, heel pull tab, and large oversized Air logo to side. Not intended for use as Personal Protective Equipment (PPE).', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091584.jpg'),
(2147, 'Air Max 90 Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Trainers in Hemp, Summit White and Earth. Originally designed for performance running, feel the purrrr of technical brilliance slot seamlessly into your everyday casual wear. Epitomising the 1990s world of art, music and culture, the striking aesthetics combine with a grippy Waffle outsole and visible lightweight Air cushioning to leave you walking on a cloud. Air technology first debuted in 1978, with its visible cousin later appearing in 1987 in the legendary Air Max 1’s.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095124.jpg'),
(2148, 'Air More Uptempo 96 Trainer', 'Nike Air More Uptempo \'96 Trainers in White, Team Red, Best Grey and Dark Beetroot. Rocking 1990’s graffiti-styled graphics and sat atop visible Air cushioning, the Air More Uptempo ’96 absolutely nails down a jaw dropping off-court aesthetic. Originally designed for performance hoops, the Max Air unit is both lightweight and durable. The elastic straps that run across the top of the foot allow you to wear them laced or unlaced, whilst the round laces match the round pull tabs for another great style point. Interior graphics, heel pull tab, and large oversized Air logo to side. Not intended for use as Personal Protective Equipment (PPE).', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4095126.jpg'),
(2149, 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07', 'Comfortable, durable and timeless—it\'s number 1 for a reason. Classic \'80s construction pairs with durable leather and Ripstop textiles for a sturdy construction. Nike Air cushioning delivers lasting comfort while reflective design details and a frosted blue outsole add bold style that tracks whether you\'re on the court or on the go.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/bff3d49a-fd0e-4471-8a97-e7973551ddb4/air-force-1-07-shoes-BpJsnm.png'),
(2150, 'Air Force 1 \'07 Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 \'07 Trainers in White, Midnight Navy and Bright Crimson. 40+ years of style, panache, charisma and running heritage all come together here with this Pegasus-inspired Air Force 1 silhouette. Secure lace fastening, durable tough stitching, immaculate materials, foam midsole and slick cupsole design. Low-cut with a padded ankle collar, perforations to toe box and multiple Swoosh logos that nod to key editions of the Pegasus. Making its first appearance in 1982, the Air Force 1 was a basketball must-have that really came into its own during the ‘90s where it blossomed from the basketball courts to the streets.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4098839.jpg'),
(2151, 'Air Force 1 Mid Trainer', 'Nike Air Force 1 Mid Trainers in Brown. A modern twist to the classic 1982 Air Force 1 trainer, honoured here on metal lace tag. With an ankle strap for a secure fit and luscious leather upper, sat atop that classic chunky Air sole.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4064635.jpg'),
(2152, 'Dunk Low Trainer', 'Nike Dunk Low White Pure Platinum Introducing your new favourite Dunk. Designed for the every day, the Nike Dunk Low Pure Platinum is a colourway that will go with every \'fit. Keeping it simple, a white base allows a light grey Swoosh, heel tab and outsole to take centre stage. A perforated toe box adds breathability and a full-length cushioned midsole delivers next-level comfort. Designed by Peter Moore in 1985, the Nike Dunk quickly became an icon on and off the courts. From its beginnings as a college basketball trainer to collaborations with Stüssy, Virgil Abloh, Supreme and Travis Scott, the Nike Dunk has cemented itself as one of the most iconic trainers of all time.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4088675.jpg'),
(2153, 'Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Trainer', 'Nike Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Trainers in Baltic Blue and Citron Tint. The Air VaporMax 2023 lights the way towards that ‘walking on Air’ sensation that only Nike can provide. Awash with innovative tech via the removable perforated sock liner and stretchy Flyknit upper that’s made from at least 20% recycled content by weight. The one-piece Air unit that patrols the entire length of the shoe allows for smoother transitions and throws in unreal levels of cushioning. Standard lacing, seamless collar that sculpts the ankle reducing hot spots, and grippy rubber outsole. After the 7-year journey from conception to release, the Air VaporMax represents a new era in Nike innovation. To truly capture the feeling of \"running on air\", the designers restructured the Air unit to be attached directly to the upper. As you step down, each lug gets pushed into the Air unit, ramping up the pressure. Then, as you step off, the pressure releases creating springy bounce with superior flexibility.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4088683.jpg'),
(2154, 'Air Max 90 Terrascape Trainer', 'Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Trainers in Cool Grey, Honeydew, Olive and Anthracite. Next up for Nike’s “Next Nature” series is this sustainable re-working of the iconic Air Max 90. Almost indistinguishable from its traditional counterpart, the lushly layered upper consists of a robust ripstop base and durable overlays, all sat upon visible Nike Air technology. The semi-translucent midsole and crater speckled outsole provide aesthetically pleasing backup. Signature Nike branding together with handy heel and tongue pull loops. This magnificent silhouette boasts around 20% recycled materials by weight, so your footprint on the earth is less impact but in no way less stylish.', 'https://www.footasylum.com/images/products/large/4091460.jpg'),
(2155, 'Nike Dunk Low', 'Created for the hardwood but taken to the streets, the Dunk returns with classic details and throwback hoops style. Its padded, low-cut collar and vintage design lets you take your game anywhere—comfortably.', 'https://static.nike.com/a/images/t_PDP_1728_v1/f_auto,q_auto:eco/6a5b4fa2-703e-4f0a-94d8-d71f714068d1/dunk-low-shoes-6JWWld.png'),
